node.text:
Talking with @berniceradle about her two cheap old house renovations. One a 10k house she bought and a 20k dollar house.

And finance tips like creative ways to afford your cheap old house go with the local bank, renovation loans, first time buyer programs, and renting out Airbnb rooms to afford projects on your house.

Ethan and I are beyond excited to welcome Ryan Gustafson of @thedeadtongues to our #CelebrationofHome concert series. We’ve been long-time fans of his music, and were honored and humbled when he offered to perform his brand new song, “Peaceful Ambassador” in this very special set just for all of you. It’s from from his new album, “Transmigration Blues,” which is coming out ‪6/26‬ and explores, in his own words, “the moments weaving between uncertainty and discovery.” (well, is that ever timely!)
.
We started our Celebration of Home series back when the world first shut down, and we realized that so many of our favorite musicians would likely be deeply affected by the shutdown. Concerts and other very large social gatherings will likely be the last things to come back to normal. And yet ironically, Ethan and I have found our salvation during this time in music. These musicians have voluntarily given their time to perform for us, and we’re so grateful to be able to share their music with all of you! The best gift you can give back to @thedeadtongues would be a follow or an album purchase from thedeadtongues.com‬
.
In the years since we’ve been running this account, we’ve noticed that musicians and other professional creatives make up a large percentage of our audience. This has not come as a surprise - it takes a creative mind to see the beauty in many of the homes we share. We’re certain you’ll see as much beauty as we do in @thedeadtongues and hope you enjoy it! Thank you Ryan!

It would be hard to convey in writing just how special this one is for me and Ethan. We started listening to @bowerbirdsmusic when we were first dating, and besides knowing every single lyric to every single album by heart (Phil is a pretty powerful lyricist), two of his songs quite literally helped inspire this feed. One, “In the Yard,” perfectly encapsulates the feeling of loving a place despite its quirks. “It may not be a grand parade of snow capped peaks...” but it’s ours.
.
The other, “House of Diamonds” (the 3rd song Phil plays in the concert) is one of my favorite songs all of time. Actually, it’s my anthem. If there’s anything I’ve preached on this feed, it’s that the American dream doesn’t have to look any one particular way.
.
“Your sister marries a nice young man; And they build a house of diamonds. But the sun is snuffed by the curtains; Can someone come untie you? But there is too much work to do. Yes, they all admire you.

You are free; You are already free.

You are free from the greed of your culture; You are free from the lust for the luster; Of the diamond houses in the city's cluster; From your own ego, from your own blunder.

Yes, you own the stars, you own the thunder
But you have to share it all;
Yes, you own the stars, you own the thunder
But you have to share.
You are free;
You are already free.”
.
Old houses in need, the ones with soul — the ones others have forgotten — are my stars and my thunder.

Phil has just released two new singles — "Endless Chase" and "Hazel Eyes" — and they have been totally worth the wait.

Anyway, I could go on and on, but at the risk of getting too sentimental about all of this, I’ll just leave it at this: Enjoy @bowerbirdsmusic - we’re honored to have him!

When Ethan and I first heard @bedouinemusic sing her song "Bird", we were stunned. Mesmerized. And she's been on steady rotation in our house ever since, filling our home with a hauntingly beautiful vintage sound (It is bossa nova? Folk? We can't tell. But it's SO good.) There's something in her voice that reminds us of the soul of old homes - which wasn't as surprising once we found out she lives in one. We hope you fall in love with her voice tonight as our #celebrationofhome concert series continues. Please enjoy, and give her a follow as thanks for being such a light in our lives (and now yours, too!)
